articles.title: Ukrainian diver with alleged links to Nord Stream attack detained in Poland - Al Jazeera
articles.description: The diver, identified as Volodymyr Z, held for 2022 explosions that largely severed Russian gas supplies to Europe.
articles.content:
A Ukrainian diver suspected of being involved in causing undersea explosions that damaged the Nord Stream gas pipelines between Russia and Germany in 2022 has been detained in Poland.
